WEBVTT

00:00.097 --> 00:01.655
<i>Previously on "Heartland"...</i>

00:01.765 --> 00:04.290
- Mom, you remember Caleb.
- Oh, of course.

00:04.401 --> 00:05.891
He's the only guy
that really gets me.

00:06.003 --> 00:07.971
Getting what he wants
is probably closer to the truth.

00:08.071 --> 00:11.735
Tim's been milking this bullet wound
like a dairy farmer with 10 hands.

00:11.842 --> 00:14.743
Do we have cheddar cheese?
Just if we do.

00:14.845 --> 00:16.437
Can't tell anyone
you're staying here, okay?

00:16.547 --> 00:18.640
Are you worried
you're gonna sully my reputation?

00:18.749 --> 00:20.148
I'm worried you're gonna sully mine.

00:20.250 --> 00:23.083
There's obviously nothing between us,
so there's nothing to explain.

00:23.187 --> 00:24.415
I have to have some tests done.

00:24.521 --> 00:26.614
My doctor is probably
just being overly cautious.

00:27.124 --> 00:28.284
You, Ty Borden.

00:28.392 --> 00:30.860
No matter what I do,
I always end up with more questions.

00:30.961 --> 00:33.088
You know those things you said
last night about your stepdad?

00:33.197 --> 00:34.425
Why didn't you ever tell me?

00:34.531 --> 00:37.329
I never told anyone
that stuff before.

00:43.407 --> 00:45.102
Jack!

00:48.178 --> 00:49.805
Hey!

00:51.381 --> 00:53.872
Sure didn't take you long
to take me up on my offer.

00:54.885 --> 00:56.978
Man gives you a gift of free hay,
you jump on it.

00:57.087 --> 00:58.987
Free?
Who said anything about free?

01:00.224 --> 01:02.556
You did. Your message.

01:02.659 --> 01:04.650
And I quote,
"Jack, you want some hay?"

01:04.760 --> 01:09.494
Yeah. I got 200 tons of hay
and two longhorns to eat it.

01:09.600 --> 01:10.589
You know what?

01:10.701 --> 01:13.693
I don't want to ruin our relationship
over 100-buck hay.

01:13.804 --> 01:15.931
75, or I'm dumping it back.

01:16.106 --> 01:20.338
75? That is a gift.

01:20.978 --> 01:22.878
What the heck?

01:29.019 --> 01:31.180
Oh, this is wonderful, dear.

01:31.288 --> 01:34.086
Sugarfoot loves your muffins.

01:34.191 --> 01:36.989
And your timing is perfect

01:37.127 --> 01:39.652
because I couldn't find
my reading glasses.

01:41.398 --> 01:42.695
Special delivery.

01:42.799 --> 01:44.562
Did I win the sweepstakes?

01:44.668 --> 01:47.136
Not exactly.

01:49.373 --> 01:52.206
It's about Sugarfoot.
From Hudson County.

01:52.342 --> 01:53.741
Hudson Derby?

01:53.844 --> 01:57.439
No, not the derby, Mrs. Bell.
They haven't run that in years.

01:57.548 --> 01:59.106
Not since the last time.

01:59.216 --> 02:02.777
Your father and your grandfather
almost killed each other.

02:02.886 --> 02:04.478
Now, what's this about Sugarfoot?

02:06.156 --> 02:07.783
I'll tell you what.

02:07.891 --> 02:11.383
Why don't I make a few calls,
take care of this for you?

02:12.863 --> 02:15.127
So, apparently you need
at least one hectare

02:15.232 --> 02:17.257
in order to keep livestock
on your property,

02:17.367 --> 02:19.267
according to this bylaw.

02:19.369 --> 02:20.495
Bylaws.

02:20.604 --> 02:21.662
And the upshot is

02:21.772 --> 02:24.900
they are threatening
to impound Sugarfoot.

02:25.008 --> 02:27.033
- Unless what?
- There is no unless.

02:27.177 --> 02:29.645
And as far as Mrs. Bell
was concerned,

02:29.746 --> 02:32.374
we're having a nice conversation
about the Hudson Derby.

02:32.482 --> 02:35.815
The Hudson Derby?
Now, that takes me back.

02:35.919 --> 02:39.013
Well, I finally found
my damn checkbook.

02:39.122 --> 02:42.455
I figure the prospect
of buying hay from you

02:42.559 --> 02:44.993
must have clouded my memory.

02:45.095 --> 02:46.323
Hey, speaking of memories, Jack,

02:46.430 --> 02:48.898
I bet you remember
the Hudson Derby.

02:48.999 --> 02:51.263
What's that got to do with anything?

02:52.269 --> 02:55.067
Last time I ever heard
anyone saying, "I'm number two!

02:55.172 --> 02:57.163
I'm number two!"

03:03.180 --> 03:04.943
Nice one, Dad.

03:07.684 --> 03:09.675
Hey, check it out.

03:10.721 --> 03:12.518
He's a real looker, hey.

03:12.623 --> 03:14.352
Yeah. Where'd you get him from?

03:14.524 --> 03:16.014
From me. His name's Money.

03:16.126 --> 03:19.618
Oh, you gave Ty a horse?
That's a pretty special present.

03:19.730 --> 03:21.459
Not really, actually.

03:21.565 --> 03:23.123
Ty said you guys
could re-home him.

03:24.167 --> 03:25.464
He did, did he?

03:25.569 --> 03:28.436
I know. I know, I know.
But I'm kind of desperate.

03:28.538 --> 03:31.098
My uncle just dumped him on me.

03:31.208 --> 03:33.540
I put an ad on the Net
about a month ago with a picture.

03:33.644 --> 03:35.043
And you know what?
So far, <i>nada.</i>

03:35.145 --> 03:38.114
Yeah. Maybe a picture
was a bad idea.

03:38.215 --> 03:40.706
Isn't he the fugliest horse
you've ever seen?

03:40.817 --> 03:42.546
But he's got a great personality.

03:42.653 --> 03:45.315
I just thought that we're all set up
for re-homing, so...

03:45.422 --> 03:48.721
Yeah. No, it's awesome.
It can be like your special project.

03:51.361 --> 03:52.350
Yeah.

03:55.799 --> 03:57.289
You know, I think you're losing it.

03:57.401 --> 03:59.733
Honestly. Your memory's shot.

03:59.836 --> 04:01.599
I won that race fair and square.

04:01.705 --> 04:05.300
No. You took a shortcut.
You should have been disqualified.

04:05.409 --> 04:07.809
Wrong side of a couple of trees.
You call that a shortcut?

04:07.911 --> 04:10.038
You went off course.
I know it. You know it.

04:10.147 --> 04:12.172
The only person that missed it
was the damn spotter.

04:12.282 --> 04:13.613
He was standing right there.

04:13.717 --> 04:15.708
If there was something to spot,
he would have spotted it.

04:15.819 --> 04:16.945
Except he was so drunk

04:17.053 --> 04:18.817
he couldn't see a foot
in front of his face

04:18.922 --> 04:20.219
'cause you bought him the whiskey.

04:20.324 --> 04:21.255
You can have the hay.

04:21.358 --> 04:23.349
- I don't want your damn hay.
- I don't want your damn money.

04:23.460 --> 04:25.587
I don't want to hear any more
about you winning that damn race!

04:25.729 --> 04:27.594
Don't worry.
I'll never mention it again.

04:27.698 --> 04:28.562
Fine!

04:32.536 --> 04:35.004
Even though you know
I won that race by three lengths.

04:35.639 --> 04:37.539
Because you cheated!

